post_text: If you are still evaluating the best options for your child this school year, come check us out. We offer online learning from the safety of your home and onsite learning as well. All of our teachers are local. That gives your child the best chances at creating those important connections with their teachers, whether they are learning online and/or onsite. We have two locations, Huntingdon & Mifflintown, but we offer online learning to students throughout PA. We're now enrolling, so give us a call at 814-643-7112. Be more at New Day Charter School. #newdaycharterschool #newday #bemoreatnewdaycharterschool #bemoreatnewday #onlineandonsiteinstruction

post_text:
Now more than ever, you may be exploring options for your childs’ education. New Day Charter School continues to provide traditional face to face instruction both online and onsite. Our Work From Home students receive the same benefits as our onsite students through our virtual learning environment. New Day is local to families in Huntingdon, Mifflin and Juniata counties, but our online program can help students across Pennsylvania. We provide one-on-one tutoring both online and onsite. New Day does not charge tuition to students or families.

Be Safe. Be Supported. Be Inspired. Be more at New Day Charter School.

Enroll now for the fall and if you have any questions, please call us at 814-643-7112. Visit our website, newdaycs.org, to learn more about us.

#newdaycharterschool #newday #bemoreatnewdaycharterschool #bemoreatnewday #onlineandonsiteinstruction

post_text:
Our online learning is an extension of our onsite classrooms. Online students receive the same instruction as our onsite students do. They are able to interact with the teachers and students on a daily basis. Our live instruction for online students gives them access to instant feedback to help answer questions or solve problems. New Day does not charge tuition to students or families.

Enroll now for the fall and if you have any questions, please call us at 814-643-7112. Visit our website, newdaycs.org, to learn more about us.

Be Safe. Be Supported. Be Inspired. Be more at New Day Charter School.

post_text:
Updated: 3/20/20

Dear Parents, Caregivers, and Students,

We will be extending our closure from Monday, March 23, to Friday, March 27, 2020. During this timeframe, teachers will be opening all past missing assignments from marking period 3 so that students have opportunities to complete them. These assignments will be opened on Monday, March 23, at 8 a.m. and closed on Friday, March 27, at 2:33. Teachers will be updating grades throughout the week and we are asking that students get in the habit of checking their email daily. It is extremely important that all students take advantage of this opportunity.

In the coming days, keep checking Facebook and www.newdaycs.org for detailed information regarding this closing and any future closing dates, any extended assignment deadlines, and essential information regarding free meals for students and free online learning resources. Feel free to reach out to us via Facebook or email if you have questions in the upcoming days.

Stay safe and we wish all of you the very best during this time.

post_text:
New Day Family,

We hope you are all doing well and taking good care during this difficult time. We understand the uncertainty this virus has caused and we are thinking of you all during this emergency. Your child and family's health and safety are most important to us. We wanted to give you the most recent COVID-19 Guidance on the State website:

https://www.education.pa.gov/Schools/safeschools/emergencyplanning/COVID-19/Pages/default.aspx

You can also find additional information put out by the Federal Government at cdc.gov.

New Day Staff is available to you. Please feel free to reach out to us during this time. We are committed to serving you. Stay safe and be well!

Autumn Fiscus, CEO, New Day Charter School

Due to impending weather, both locations of New Day Charter School will be on a work from home schedule, Tuesday, December 17. We are NOT running on a delayed schedule even though other schools delayed. We will continue to work from home and run a normal time schedule from 7:45am - 3:15pm. Teachers will be teaching all classes online and students will need to log into every class (except homeroom and lunch) via the online classrooms link on the www.newdaycs.org website and complete any assignments required by the teacher in order to be counted in attendance.

The student holiday meal will be moved to Wednesday, December 18. text:
Due to impending weather, both locations of New Day Charter School will be on a work from home schedule, Tuesday, December 17. We are NOT running on a delayed schedule even though other schools delayed. We will continue to work from home and run a normal time schedule from 7:45am - 3:15pm. Teachers will be teaching all classes online and students will need to log into every class (except homeroom and lunch) via the online classrooms link on the www.newdaycs.org website and complete any assignments required by the teacher in order to be counted in attendance.

The student holiday meal will be moved to Wednesday, December 18. Seniors are welcome to come in to school for the holiday meal; but, if they do, they will need to come into school and leave following their normal arrival departure schedule (read: seniors have to spend a normal day at school if they want to come for the meal).
